%
% An elliptic curvilinear grating
%
% The adjustable parameters are as follows:
% 
% theta1 - the angle of the first axis of the elliptic grating, in degrees.
% p1 - the radial period of the elliptic grating along its first axis, in
%	centiinches.
% rad - the radius of the elliptic grating along its first axis, in centiinches.
% ratio - the ratio between the radiuses along the first and the second axes.
% lwidth - the linewidth, in centiinches.
%
% ********************************************************************************
%





% ************ Adjustable parameters for the curvilinear grating:


/theta1 0 def		% angle of the first axis of the elliptic grating in degrees

/p1 3 def		% radial period of the elliptic grating along its first axis 
			% in centiinches
/rad 330 def		% radius of the elliptic grating along its first axis 
			% in centiinches
/ratio 1.3 def		% the ratio between the radiuses along the first and the 
			% second axes
/lwidth 1.0 def		% linewidth in centiinches





% ************ Draw the circular grating:

/inch {72 mul} def

/centiinch {0.72 mul} def

0.15 inch 3.0 inch translate


lwidth centiinch setlinewidth


gsave
4 inch 4 inch translate
theta1 rotate
1 ratio scale

/firstrad p1 2.0 div def
newpath
firstrad p1 rad		% draw circles
{/r exch def
 0 0 r centiinch 0 360 arc stroke
} for
grestore


gsave
1.75 inch -1.0 inch translate
0.5 inch 0 inch moveto
